Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.63,0:55:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,save the rabbit's life. No. The brake was on when it, it had already happened. I caught
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.01,0:55:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it. It's one ten-thousandth of a second. It takes one ten-thousandth of a second for the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.73,0:56:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencer to move from the phenomena to the subjective readout. So reality is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.01,0:56:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,like the actual reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.61,0:56:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The activity in the world, in the readout, what you're getting through your ego, is like
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.59,0:56:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the old tape recorder, the tape monitor. So the ego is your tape monitor, which is one
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.84,0:56:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,ten-thousandth of a second after the reality has happened. So perception is one ten-thousandth
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.61,0:56:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of a second behind what is. And it's a shock when that, that's, when the monitoring stops,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.48,0:56:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and the awareness and the experiencing are simultaneous. And that's what gives the highest
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.21,0:56:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,level their extraordinary quality. Because when the door opens up, you're paralyzed,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.55,0:57:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you're knocked out by the brilliance and the radiance of divinity as all that exists. All
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.48,0:57:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that exists is divinity. The radiance of the divinity shines forth with such a stunning
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.98,0:57:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,beauty that you're immobile.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.36,0:57:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Subtitles by the Amara.org community
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.11,0:57:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not able to function, think, and from that moment on, all has changed, all changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.92,0:57:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so perception that is mental, the isness of things is something you intuit without thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.11,0:57:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason that contemplation is so useful, and I recommend it as a spiritual style,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.90,0:57:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is because contemplation is a lifestyle, it's a way of being with reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.15,0:57:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of being open.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.44,0:57:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditation, as I've said before, it serves a purpose, but it takes you out of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.01,0:57:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Being contemplative, you're always in, you might say, a meditative state about everything all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.26,0:58:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't give any more attention to this than you do to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.55,0:58:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't give any attention, more attention to the left side of the aisle than the right side of the aisle.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.84,0:58:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor do I give either side of the aisle greater attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.17,0:58:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And then being aware of the walls in the room, or of the light coming in from above,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.48,0:58:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or the color of the rug, the green, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.73,0:58:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, the totality is equally valued, you might say, equally experienced at all times,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.11,0:58:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,within which phenomena are occurring, yeah, within which.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.00,0:58:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Within which perception, it doesn't that perception stops, but because it's modified by essence,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.82,0:58:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it has a different quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.73,0:58:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It has a different value.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.07,0:58:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception makes distinctions, and essence is the allness and the oneness of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.88,0:58:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception, therefore, is motivated and is selective.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.46,0:59:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very personal.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.55,0:59:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Essence is witnessed, it's the totality, it's impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.09,0:59:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It registers, but it does so passively.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.09,0:59:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't seek it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.21,0:59:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not trying to.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.76,0:59:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not trying to accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.63,0:59:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not trying to experience the silence of the woods as you walk through the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.55,0:59:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not straining to hear the silence, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.19,0:59:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet the silence is one of the most profound aspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.57,0:59:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the silence, then the sound of a twig becomes highly meaningful.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.36,0:59:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Not every twig sounds the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.65,0:59:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear a twig snap, and you hear a twig snap, and suddenly when you hear this twig snap,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.07,0:59:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you whirl because that's the sound of a bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.23,0:59:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Those were not the sound of a bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.13,0:59:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you know this is the sound of a bear?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.69,0:59:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.30,0:59:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd never experienced the sound of a bear behind you before.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.17,0:59:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's a knowingness of the field that somehow that twig snap is different somehow
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.90,1:00:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,than the other twig snaps.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.96,1:00:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The other twig snaps have a certain benignness.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.63,1:00:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This one had a loud crunch to it that something inside your animal,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.73,1:00:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,ancient animal knows that that's the sound of a binging.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.09,1:00:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And you whirl around, and it is the bear.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.07,1:00:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you didn't know the bear was there.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.84,1:00:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you whirl on this one?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.71,1:00:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So there was a prior knowingness there on a subliminal level.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.42,1:00:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.11,1:00:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.57,1:00:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning, therefore, is a projection.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.07,1:00:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is only concerned with things being that they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.44,1:00:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception is, therefore, motivated.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.78,1:00:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Essence is witnessed.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.55,1:00:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is selective.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.76,1:00:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.71,1:00:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This is want, don't want.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.23,1:00:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is merely observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.28,1:00:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, the memory is filed according to feeling states.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.03,1:00:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Research shows that memories, it's the feeling associated with the memory
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.21,1:01:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that selects where these flowers are filed.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.48,1:01:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And this memory bank are filed under pretty.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.53,1:01:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They're filed under pleasant, good, smell good.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.59,1:01:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an affective tone to all memories.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.96,1:01:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And the memory banks are filed according to affective tone.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.07,1:01:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that interesting?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.90,1:01:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Not linear content like dogs and cats, but the cozy, the dog and cat is cozy lovingness,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.55,1:01:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,pet, friend kind of feeling.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.76,1:01:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In that file, you find the cozy, cuddly, happy, waggy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.73,1:01:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's where dog and kitty are.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.00,1:01:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not filed under domestic animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.48,1:01:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Domestic animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.71,1:01:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.84,1:01:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So the memory file.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.30,1:01:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Interesting is shaded by affect.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.96,1:01:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you think about a thing and here you know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.09,1:02:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no thinking about what could be said.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.36,1:02:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, right now, speaking this here.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.94,1:02:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This speaking this here, you can't think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.63,1:02:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Where would you get the time to think about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.36,1:02:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.86,1:02:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You either have to know it and you speak.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.67,1:02:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So the knowingness speaks because it does it right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.36,1:02:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you'd have to think about it, which is a whole different deal, you know, thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.38,1:02:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This would require evaluation and this you're just to recognize the purity of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.84,1:02:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is processed and therefore somewhat contaminated.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.73,1:02:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception is very, very programmable.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.01,1:02:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you hear people make comments about politics, what they're usually pulling
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.61,1:02:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,out is a blog site and a bunch of memes.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.92,1:02:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They're just like parrots.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.71,1:02:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They've been parrot, parrots, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.23,1:02:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And they think that's their opinion.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.86,1:02:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's got nothing to do with their opinion.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.67,1:03:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a program that they picked up, either, you know, subliminally or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.36,1:03:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Quarter of?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.92,1:03:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We're okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.55,1:03:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.42,1:03:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.86,1:03:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Perceptual influences.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.21,1:03:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of consciousness obviously determines considerably because your dedication
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.32,1:03:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to truth makes you very aware that the media are programming you all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.65,1:03:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And you hold back belief because you know
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.96,1:03:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,there's going to be more to the story.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.25,1:03:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And those who have lived long enough know that sometimes 20 or 25 years,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.25,1:03:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the stories of what really happened in World War II are still being revealed.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.15,1:03:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still being revealed.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.17,1:03:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There were things that are still coming out.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.36,1:03:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So you hold back judgment because the whole story obviously is not out yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.84,1:03:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Not out yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.73,1:03:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And the level of consciousness then has to do, you might say,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.63,1:03:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhat with sophistication in a certain way.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.30,1:03:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.53,1:03:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.15,1:04:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception is therefore programmable, conditioned, depends again on set and setting and priority.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.48,1:04:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And whether people like it or not, age, sex, and gender play a big role, a very big role.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.28,1:04:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And you hear people protest that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.00,1:04:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You're fooling yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.05,1:04:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, the age is going to determine how you evaluate that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.78,1:04:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Men see certain things as more fun than women do, and vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.30,1:04:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Gender certainly has a big effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.15,1:04:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If I walk down the street, I'll notice a new dress in the storefront, and she notices them.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.19,1:04:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.69,1:04:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because dresses don't interest me, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.32,1:04:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't wear them.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.96,1:04:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, gender plays a role in how you perceived it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.86,1:04:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Fifth Avenue is either fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.76,1:04:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Gucci's and all those stores are either fun or not fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.40,1:04:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I think they're boring.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.17,1:05:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've got a good set of shoes, I don't know where you want to go there.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.57,1:05:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what you're going to wear there for, but anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.57,1:05:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, just to be very smart, you know, people like to hang out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.57,1:05:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so your education, the culture which you come from, your emotional set, the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.25,1:05:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,media play, the propaganda, the hype, the glamorization, the status symbols that become
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.90,1:05:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,associated with that, you know, your label.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.90,1:05:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't know, it's a person wearing a label or a label wearing a person sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.30,1:05:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You see a label walking down the street, and there's a person and a person attached to
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.65,1:05:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.53,1:05:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is all very seductive, and it has a very personal meaning.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.94,1:05:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Not that it's wrong, but to see that that's what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.03,1:05:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Some things have an instinctual appeal, and your prior experience and exposure will certainly
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.78,1:05:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,determine your expectation and how you interpret it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.67,1:06:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, your political viewpoint will skew it one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.26,1:06:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Many things don't have a specific meaning in themself, but they're very powerful because
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.96,1:06:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,they have become a symbol.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.07,1:06:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The emotional projections onto a symbol become very, very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.30,1:06:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And there again, they're in the memory file according to, and they're framed according
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.51,1:06:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to specific meanings.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.73,1:06:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How you frame a thing will very profoundly alter how you interpret it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.88,1:06:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we mean by how you frame it?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.32,1:06:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The same situation, when looked at differently, from a different perspective, now seems different.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.05,1:06:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That of course is the course of miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.44,1:06:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The course of miracles is really a course in reframing, reframing.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.36,1:06:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You take it out of the immediate present, instead of projecting your own ego onto it,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.73,1:06:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you turn it over to the Holy Spirit.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.23,1:06:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What you mean is you allow God to give it a greater context, and in a greater context,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.26,1:07:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,it means something totally different, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.01,1:07:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw him as a terrible, frightening enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.42,1:07:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And now in a greater context, you see what he is, driven by something, and obviously
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.26,1:07:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,a teacher of yours, and et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.01,1:07:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore, the way a thing is framed, and one way to heal things is to merely reframe
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.38,1:07:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,them.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.86,1:07:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And I used to do a lot of that in therapy when I did psychiatry for many years, is I
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.63,1:07:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,would just reframe it, and then say, now, if you looked at it this way, then how would
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.44,1:07:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it look?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.42,1:07:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, if I held it that way, then it would look differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.03,1:07:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.03,1:07:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what the Holy Spirit does.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.26,1:07:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When you surrender it, you allow the field to reframe it, and now when it's reframed,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.38,1:07:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,taken out of context, out of time, and out of the concept of causality, it's totally
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.80,1:07:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,different.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.84,1:07:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So your level of spiritual evolution will determine your opinions and intentions.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.84,1:07:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the next slide, and I think we have only one left after this, correct?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.84,1:08:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.46,1:08:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this the last one, or is the second the last?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.53,1:08:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.90,1:08:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.90,1:08:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.98,1:08:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.98,1:08:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.98,1:08:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.98,1:08:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How to get off hate, you know, alternate viewpoints.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.53,1:08:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,People are upset with hate.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.11,1:08:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They feel guilty about it, and yet they see things as hateful and evil, and at the same
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.56,1:08:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,time, they feel guilty, and they hate themselves for hating.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.85,1:08:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They feel guilty about hating.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.68,1:08:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the idea that evil is in the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.36,1:08:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the idea that evil is in the present.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.36,1:08:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the idea that death is in the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.36,1:08:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the idea that it's in the eye of the beholder.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.36,1:08:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a hard one, because if you calibrate things, it's not just in the eye of the beholder.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.36,1:08:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be just in the eye of the beholder.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.92,1:08:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, it cannot even be in the eye of the beholder and be out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.65,1:08:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.97,1:08:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's different ways of looking at all the horrible people that have been in your
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.35,1:08:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,life and who deserve to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.61,1:09:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Slow and painfully.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.30,1:09:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Slowly, slowly.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.42,1:09:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hehehe.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.42,1:09:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hehehe.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.65,1:09:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hehehe.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.18,1:09:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,they've earned every turn of the screw
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.31,1:09:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,so first give yourself a gleeful chance
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.73,1:09:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to torture them
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.84,1:09:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,call them all kinds of horrible names
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.06,1:09:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and get over it
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.23,1:09:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,now if you don't hate somebody
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.22,1:09:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't hate them enough, that's your problem
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.68,1:09:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to hate them more
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.30,1:09:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,they are awful, they stink
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.52,1:09:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,they're awful
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.06,1:09:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you just gotta hate them a lot harder
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.81,1:09:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot harder, a lot harder
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.43,1:09:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you'll see that what they're suffering from
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.25,1:09:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,could be viewed as a sad mistake
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.90,1:09:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry you ran across my new lawn with your truck
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.51,1:09:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that was a sad mistake
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.21,1:09:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to kill them after all
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.85,1:10:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,first get killing them out of your blood
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.71,1:10:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and get it over with
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.47,1:10:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,have a good time, chop them to small pieces
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.52,1:10:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,burn them at the stake
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.44,1:10:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to kill them
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.56,1:10:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,all right you can see that it
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.18,1:10:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we can say that that's a sad mistake
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.10,1:10:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the history of world war two
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.77,1:10:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,one sad mistake after another
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.42,1:10:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you see reruns of world war two
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.61,1:10:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.27,1:10:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and the other side he was visiting his wife on D-day
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.57,1:10:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and the great general that was supposed to defend Germany
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.85,1:10:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Raoul, yeah, it was his wife's birthday
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.65,1:10:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it was his wife's birthday
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.42,1:10:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the day he was needed more than any other day in the entire world
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.85,1:10:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the day he was needed more than any other day in the entire world
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.85,1:10:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,he was visiting his wife's birthday
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.85,1:10:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,oh god, yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.43,1:10:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,he could say a naive error
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.77,1:10:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,on the other hand didn't it come out of his passion for life
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.84,1:10:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it came out of his love for his wife, did it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.84,1:11:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.88,1:11:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we can see people as duped and misled
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.88,1:11:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we can see that they're programmed and brainwashed
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.88,1:11:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you can certainly see that
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.88,1:11:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in islamic terrorism
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.88,1:11:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact they systematically brainwashed them
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.88,1:11:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact they even admit that they brainwashed them
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.88,1:11:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see other people's behaviors as some kind of a karmic propensity
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.88,1:11:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of which they really have no conscious memory
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.88,1:11:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see it of course as Christ's ignorance
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.88,1:11:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I commonly see distinct character traits of mentally ill psychopathic personalities
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.55,1:11:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,due to a genetic defect
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.55,1:11:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand the serial killer cannot
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.55,1:11:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,there was the most gruesome one I've heard in years
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.55,1:11:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,just about a week ago
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.57,1:11:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and what this guy was going to do with this little girl
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.57,1:11:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to hear about it
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.57,1:11:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.57,1:11:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,about as bad as you can get
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.57,1:11:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,what does that calibrate?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.57,1:11:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it's probably around 10
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.57,1:11:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,10 or 15
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.85,1:12:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,pathetic, some kind of a karmic propensity
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.85,1:12:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,based on ignorance
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.85,1:12:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and the person is obviously mentally ill
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.85,1:12:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, mentally ill
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.01,1:12:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,alright, so there's a genetic defect in the psychopathic criminal personality
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.01,1:12:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the criminality is diagnosable by age 3
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.01,1:12:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the genetic propensity to criminality is diagnosed by age 3
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.32,1:12:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the psychologist puts a candy there
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.61,1:12:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,says I'm going to leave for a minute
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.61,1:12:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be back in one minute
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.61,1:12:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,if you don't touch it, I'll give you five
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.84,1:12:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the normal child can withstand for one minute
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.84,1:12:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,psychologist comes out, one minute later
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.86,1:12:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it's still there
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.86,1:12:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you reward the child
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.86,1:12:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the psychopathic personality by age 3
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.86,1:12:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot do it for one minute
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.86,1:12:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,psychologist walks out
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.85,1:12:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of getting five pieces of candy
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.65,1:12:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot tolerate one minute of frustration
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.65,1:12:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that's already diagnosable by age 3
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.19,1:13:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's a congenital defect in the prefrontal cortex
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.19,1:13:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the gray matter is actually thinner
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.19,1:13:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the inability to control one's behavior
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.19,1:13:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,alright, so you can say there's a genetic defect
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.23,1:13:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,obviously this person who has planned this most gruesome of all crimes
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.23,1:13:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,which, you know, was on the TV last week
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.23,1:13:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and doesn't bear description
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.23,1:13:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,obviously has a genetic defect
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.23,1:13:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,alright, so we could say the person was vulnerable
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.68,1:13:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,they were duped
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.68,1:13:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,they were dominated by some energy
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.68,1:13:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,like a person we were talking about at lunch
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.68,1:13:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,who had many years sober
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.68,1:13:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and then got a gambling addiction
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.75,1:13:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and thought he could make up his mind not to gamble
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.75,1:13:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,he could go into a casino and not gamble
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.75,1:13:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but if you've ever been walked through a casino
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.96,1:13:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a very distinct energy to a casino
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.96,1:13:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and every time I walk through them I usually do so briskly
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.96,1:13:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,there's an energy pulling like this
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.96,1:13:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a seductive energy
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.96,1:13:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and so he lost it
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.96,1:14:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and now the last phone call I got from him
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.96,1:14:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,he's lost everything, everything
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.96,1:14:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,house, family, wife, everything
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.96,1:14:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,wiped out
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.96,1:14:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't lose his sobriety but
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.27,1:14:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,wiped out
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.35,1:14:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's energy dominated
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.50,1:14:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that energy field hits you in the solar plexus
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.50,1:14:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're a goner, alright
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.92,1:14:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,alternate viewpoints is that they're not evil but infantile
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.92,1:14:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're very primitive
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.92,1:14:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,very atavistic meaning very primitive
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.92,1:14:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and you know Freud's theory in
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.92,1:14:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the depth of the id
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.92,1:14:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the depth of the id
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.92,1:14:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the id is the most
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.92,1:14:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the pits in the unconscious
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.94,1:14:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is what you know
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.61,1:14:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud postulated eros
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.61,1:14:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,eros, love, the energy of life
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.61,1:14:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,he also postulated
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.44,1:14:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to explain other inexplicable behavior
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.44,1:14:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,thanatos, the energy of death
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.44,1:14:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see if there is such a thing
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.44,1:15:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we have permission to do this right now
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.80,1:15:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,within Freud's id is thanatos
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.07,1:15:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and thanatos is an operating energy
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.11,1:15:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,there's this
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.11,1:15:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't like the answer but it says yes
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.31,1:15:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that within the id there's also the attraction to death
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.31,1:15:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the attraction to death
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.31,1:15:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to play with death
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.31,1:15:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to challenge death
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.85,1:15:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to flirt with death
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.32,1:15:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,skydiving
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.32,1:15:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you know all the things where you flirt with death
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.32,1:15:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and the thrill is seeing how close you can get to the candle and not get burned
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.59,1:15:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course as we said from non-linear dynamics
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.59,1:15:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you can get close to the candle only so many times and then bang
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.59,1:15:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,gotcha
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.59,1:15:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,bang, gotcha
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.59,1:15:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in non-linear dynamics you cannot predict
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.59,1:15:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you can do a four
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.59,1:15:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,four gainer many times
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.59,1:15:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and then one day
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.59,1:15:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody says
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.64,1:15:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what about your mother's birthday
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.64,1:15:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that's it
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.64,1:15:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the foot slips and goodbye
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.64,1:16:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so there's an attraction to death itself
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.64,1:16:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't that weird
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.64,1:16:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,thanatos counterbalanced by eros
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.97,1:16:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,alternative viewpoints is that the people are socially coerced
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.97,1:16:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,many people behave in certain ways because their society
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.97,1:16:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,has a profound influence
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.42,1:16:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,negative emotional storm
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.42,1:16:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,people snapped
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.71,1:16:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,let's do snapped
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.71,1:16:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to do snapped
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.71,1:16:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we got time to do snapped
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.71,1:16:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we got permission to do snapped
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.84,1:16:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,snapped calibrates to 90
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.84,1:16:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,100
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.84,1:16:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,95
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.51,1:16:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,100
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.51,1:16:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,snapped is about 95
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.51,1:16:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,calibration level 95
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.51,1:16:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the emotional storm is such
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.51,1:16:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,negative emotional storm
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.51,1:16:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and they say what happened he snapped
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.51,1:16:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I always loved that diagnosis
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.51,1:16:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,snapped
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.51,1:16:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,there's another explanation
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.61,1:16:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the compartmentalized personality
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.61,1:17:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,this is very common in informants whistleblowers
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.61,1:17:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,people like we recently in the CIA
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.61,1:17:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,intelligence departments
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.61,1:17:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the Manhattan project
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.61,1:17:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,turncoats
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.61,1:17:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,espionage agents have compartmentalized personalities
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.61,1:17:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes they know about the other personality
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.61,1:17:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes they do not
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.61,1:17:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the book truth versus false
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.61,1:17:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,would we diagnose several of them
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.61,1:17:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,they are quite famous
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.61,1:17:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,quite famous
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.61,1:17:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,famous, the expert group and etc. had some compartmentalized personalities. Some
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.22,1:17:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,people well-known in the public had a Jacqueline High personality, a
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.31,1:17:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,personality disorder. Then you have narcissistic megalomania. I don't think
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.80,1:17:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,people like these crazy dictators have any control. I don't think they have any
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.61,1:17:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,possibility of control. All 300 million have to die. They don't have any control
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.65,1:17:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,over that. Okay, so let them die. We will prepare an atomic bomb that will now
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.38,1:17:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,kill all of life. It will kill all of human life forever. I don't think they
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.50,1:18:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,can control that. Psychosis, you might call it a psychosis. Impulse disorder,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.84,1:18:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,psychopathy, just plain ignorance. Driven compulsion, intoxication, intoxication.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.76,1:18:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,They're misinformed. They're delusional. See, instead of hating them, you can see
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.39,1:18:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're ill. You can see they're a member of a subculture. There's a lack of
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.42,1:18:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual evolution. There's regression and degeneration. All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.55,1:18:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And how do you handle it? With acceptance. You accept that all these factors, you
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.43,1:18:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,have compassion for them. You understand that this person has no capacity to do
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.10,1:18:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,other than, be other than that which they are. It doesn't mean you have to
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.57,1:18:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,become their victim. The fault of the far left is because of this, now you need to
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.73,1:18:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,become their victim. No, you need to know this and not become their victim. Because
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.35,1:18:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you feel sorry for them,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.56,1:19:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't mean you have to allow them to run over you with a tractor. Yeah. Acceptance
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.77,1:19:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and self-compassion doesn't mean passivity, to willingly assist that which is destructive
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.77,1:19:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,through understanding, tolerance, patience, forbearance, and because you yourself have
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.53,1:19:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,become benign, these alternate ways of looking at it are welcome because you're very glad
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.39,1:19:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to be rid of hatred and anger.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.81,1:19:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very unpleasant to hate anything, is it not? You don't like yourself for hating
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.56,1:19:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it. There's a certain narcissistic juice you get out of it. But overall if you're always
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.56,1:19:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritually committed, you don't feel good about the fact that you hate something,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.06,1:19:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't go around모 AND ANNOUNCING ALL YOUR HATREDS, YOU KNOW, FOR ADMIRATION BY SOCIETY
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.14,1:19:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,OR YOUR FAMILY, YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING? We always look at them as some kind of a defect,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.81,1:19:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and we ask God to help us get over our hatred.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.81,1:19:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,ZACH DENISON SAID, YOU CAN'T AFFORD THIS. OR YOU CAN'T AFFORD THIS. IF YOU CAN'T HAVE
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.81,1:19:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,IT, I CAN'T MAKE IT. ZACH DENISON SAID, WHAT IF YOU CAN'T PUT IT IN YOUR MOUTH? IT'S A POTENTIAL
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.81,1:20:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,hatred. And the way, at least my own experience has been, is that the Holy Spirit reframes
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.43,1:20:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it, reframes it. And now when it's reframed, you see it differently. And you feel compassion
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.60,1:20:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,for the person, and you see them, they're fulfilling their own karmic potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.07,1:20:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what they're doing. And of course, in the language of the Course, they become
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.07,1:20:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,your teacher. They become your teacher. So the hateful ones are then secretly your teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.07,1:20:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because now you're forced to see them differently. A sad mistake. I like sad mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.07,1:20:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's pretty good. You look back on your own life, anything that happened, you can
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.07,1:20:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,say, well, that was a sad mistake. Eventually you reach the point where choosing to get
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.64,1:20:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,born again was a sad mistake. But anyway, here we are.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.64,1:21:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I think that does. Is that 89, sweetheart? Okay. So we've run through most of 89 slides,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.77,1:21:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,which covers an incredible amount of territory, a huge, staggering amount of information.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.77,1:21:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And even assimilating small bits of it, it already begins to change how you see the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.77,1:21:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,how you react, how you see the world changes, as a consequence of which you react differently
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.77,1:21:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to the world. And because you react differently to the world, because you react differently
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.77,1:21:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to the world, you love yourself more. And because you love yourself more, you can be
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.77,1:21:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,more benign towards the world. And because you're more benign towards the world, the
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.77,1:21:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,world treats you more benignly. And you can see that it's a self-fulfillment of your own
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.77,1:21:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,potential. So we'll meet again later, after a short break. What time do we have to be
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.77,1:21:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,back? What?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.09,1:21:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,3 o'clock, which is now.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.59,1:21:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We take a break from 2.45 to 3, which we just blew, because I lost track of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.52,1:22:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, why don't we be back in 15 minutes, which is 25 after, just so you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.59,1:22:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.59,1:22:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Doc, if you don't mind, if you want just your book signed, please line up on the right side.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.59,1:22:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.59,1:22:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you wanted to ask Dr. Hawkins a question, please line up on the left side.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.59,1:22:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a cut-off point to the lining up, because we have a short amount of time, and
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.59,1:22:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll see you in 15.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.59,1:22:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot to tell you, essence is timeless. Time doesn't mean anything. I don't know
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.59,1:22:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened to time.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.84,1:22:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody stole my time. They stole my time, and I don't know what they did with it.
